Defendant Jessica K Lentz in court with attorney M. Elizabeth Weathers.  Brian J. Juech appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.
  The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

Count #1:

  The Defendant was given the following:

WITHHELD SENTENCE;

TERM OF PROBATION:  2 YEAR(S); (probation may be transferred to Milwaukee County).

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AGENT TO DETERMINE - AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended; 
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain full time employment and/or combination of schooling 
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.
*No association with known drug users or dealers and no contact at any place where illegal drugs are purchased, used, stored, packaged, or distributed.
*100 Hours Community Service. 

COURT COSTS:  $268.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $250.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

CONDITION TIME: 30 DAYS - non working hours. Last 10 DAYS STAYED; to be used at agent's discretion.  Agent to determine with or without non working hours.  (may be served in Milwaukee County but the Court DOES NOT AUTHORIZE ELECTRONIC MONITORING). Defendant to report  to the Huber Facility by 5:00 p.m. on Monday, May 9, 2016.

Expunction is conditionally granted upon verification of completion of sentence, payment of all costs/fees and no new criminal law violations.

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
